# Security Audit Ignore File
# Mark false positives to filter them out automatically
#
# Format: filepath:line:VULN_TYPE  # optional comment
#
# Examples:
#   auth.py:47:SQL_INJECTION  # test code, safe
#   views.py:23:XSS  # input is sanitized elsewhere
#   utils.py:*:COMMAND_INJECTION  # ignore all occurrences in this file
#
# Supported wildcards:
#   - Use * for line number to ignore all occurrences in a file
#   - Use just filename (not full path) for portability
#
# Vulnerability types:
#   SQL_INJECTION, XSS, COMMAND_INJECTION, PATH_TRAVERSAL,
#   INSECURE_DESERIALIZATION, WEAK_CRYPTO, HARDCODED_SECRET,
#   SSRF, XXE, LDAP_INJECTION, etc.
#
# Add your ignore rules below:

